title: Visit by Prime Minister Kevin Rudd of Australia to Washington | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House




February 26, 2009

 



Visit by Prime Minister Kevin Rudd of Australia to Washington






THE WHITE HOUSE

		Office of the Press Secretary

		_____________________________________

		For Immediate Release                  February 26, 2009

		President Obama will meet with Prime Minister Kevin Rudd of Australia at the White House on Tuesday, March 24.  Australia is a close ally of the United States.  The President looks forward to discussing with the Prime Minister ways to address critical global issues.  The two leaders will consult on effective measures to respond to the global financial crisis, as well as Afghanistan, climate change, nuclear nonproliferation, and other issues.  

		THE WHITE HOUSE, February 26, 2009.
